reply_text:
@thechosen5767 Furhman testified normally earlier in the trial. When it came out later that he lied about using the n word, Furhmans lawyer advised him to plead the fifth to avoid incriminating himself. He did so, pleading the 5th to "all further questions." You can not pick and choose questions once you make that statement. 
It was only AFTER Furhman said he would not answer ANY questions, that of course, the defense decided to ask him "did you plant evidence." Because they were just told they were guaranteed to get a plead-the-fifth response! Good move by defense to make him look bad.
If you have any evidence Furhman planted anything, you can share it.
